    "created_at": "2015-06-16T02:49:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-16T02:57:07Z",
    "body": "Would an app `activate`/`deactivate` event make more sense (currently there is only `activate-with-no-open-windows`)?\n\nI tend to think that window focus/blur should be triggered by the window and only the window. It's trivial to shim this and create your own event on the app instance if desired. There are lots of events on window that could be exposed on the app instance too but it seems like it could be a rabbit hole to do so.\n"
  },
