    "created_at": "2016-04-02T18:15:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-02T18:15:20Z",
    "body": "Did we ever get app `activate` / `deactivate` events?  I see `activate` the [app docs](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/api/app.md), but it's only for OS X, and there is no `deactivate` event, as far as I can tell.\n\nSpecifically, I need to know when the _application_ itself is activated or deactivated, not at the window level.  Specifically, I need to hide all my `alwaysOnTop` windows on app deactivate, and show them again on app activate.  But I don't want to take any action if the user is just focusing / blurring windows within my app.\n\nThanks!\n"
